# Threading & UI Safety

All I/O, downloads, and network calls **must** run in background daemon threads — never block the main (UI) thread.

## Main-Thread Dispatcher

Use `queue.Queue[Callable[[], None]]` + `self.after(16, self._drain_main_queue)` to marshal callbacks from worker threads to the main thread. Background threads call `_call_on_main(func)` to schedule work on the UI thread.

## Rules

- **Daemon threads only** — set `daemon=True` on all background `threading.Thread` instances.
- **`DownloadManager` must never import or reference UI widgets.** Communicate results via callbacks (`progress_callback`, `item_done_callback`, `done_callback`).
- **Cancellation** — use `threading.Event` (`_cancel_event`). Never kill threads.
- **Single background thread per download session** — no thread pools. Sequential batch downloads use one thread iterating over URLs.
- **Progress throttling** — `_on_progress` skips `downloading` events within 50 ms of the last one to reduce main-queue flooding.
- **`self.after()` timers** for periodic main-thread work (clipboard polling, queue processing). Keep intervals consistent with existing values (16 ms queue drain, 1000 ms clipboard).
